A driver was entrapped after his truck collided with a tree on Essex Terrace, Westville, near Neptune Rd last night (4 May) at about 6pm.According to Ceron Lennox of Rescue Care when paramedics arrived at the scene they found that a single truck had collided into a tree. Paramedics worked together with the Durban Fire Department to stabilise the patient and then cut the man free using the Jaws of Life. The man refused to go to hospital for further care after advanced life support paramedics assisted him. Police are investigating the accident. &nbsp;